        <briefdescription>
<para>Driver for Pin interrupt and pattern match engine in NXP MCUs. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>The Pin interrupt and pattern match engine (PINT) supports sourcing inputs from any pins on GPIO ports 0 and 1 of NXP MCUs featuring the module, and generating interrupts based on these inputs. Pin inputs can generate separate interrupts to the NVIC, or be combined using the PINT&apos;s boolean logic based pattern match engine. This driver currently only supports the pin interrupt feature of the PINT.</para>
<para>Pin interrupt sources</para>
<para>Pin interrupt sources available for use. </para>
        </detaileddescription>
